			<h3 style=3D"text-align: center;"><strong>The Difference Between Psi And=
 Bar: Which Is Their Relationship With Atmospheres?</strong></h3>
<p>As scuba divers, we also use atmospheres (ATM) as a pressure measure. An=
 atmosphere measures the pressure&nbsp;exerted&nbsp;by the weight&nbsp;of t=
he atmosphere&nbsp;on all bodies. At sea level, that pressure is approximat=
ely 14.7 PSI =3D 1.013 BAR =3D 1 ATM.</p>
